        <li>If you deployed this app by deploying the Heroku Button, then in a command line shell, run:</li>
        <ul>
          <li><code>git clone https://github.com/DhavalDalal/geographic-services.git</code> - this will create a local copy of the source code for the app</li>
          <li><code>cd geographic-services</code> - change directory into the local source code repository</li>
          <li><code>heroku git:remote -a &lt;your-app-name></code> or <code>git remote add heroku https://git.heroku.com/your-app-name.git</code> - associate the Heroku app with the repository</li>
          <li>You'll now be set up to run the app locally, or <a href="https://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/getting-started-with-nodejs#push-local-changes">deploy changes</a> to Heroku</li>
